I made this dish for the third time over the weekend for a potluck. This time I made some changes. I found the slices of polenta from the roll remained too firm after cooking even though I used the whipping cream on top of each slice, so I substituted Trader Joes frozen Creamy Polenta With Spinach and Carrots with about half a polenta roll, cut in pieces incorporated into the prepared polenta. I added the ½ cup of whipping cream to the polenta. I used half golden hominy and half white hominy. Chopping the cilantro is tedious but worth it, and I used Trader Joes Salsa Verde. The cheese was a mixture of cheddar and Jack. Everything else was according to the recipe, except I wanted to use a glass baking dish that was a little bit longer and a little bit deeper than my 11x7x2 one so I increased all ingredients by about 1/3. It turned out beautiful and delicious. I will make it again.

