Rating: 3
Made this last night as we headed into predicted 3 day string of subzero temps. It was delicious and would be a quickie to prep but for washing, drying, chopping cilantro (but cilantro adds so much to the dish). Here's what I did differently: 1) lowered oven temp to 325 so I could use a ceramic oval baker; 2) sauteed 1/2 onion with garlic cloves then added to chili mixture; 3) used entire 4 oz. can of salsa verde; 4) "dolloped" each polenta coin with about 1 tsp of fat free sour cream instead of using whipping cream; 5) used a pre-packaged "Mexican" (not taco-flavored) shredded cheese mix; 6) reduced cheese used to 2 cups (about 3/4 c on first layer; 1 1/4 on second--you won't miss the extra cup); 7) ground a little fresh black pepper on the sour cream layers; 8) baked at 325 covered with foil for 30 min; uncovered for 15 until golden; and 9) garnished with the 1/4 c cilantro and 2 chopped green onions. It was very tasty, family loved it and I am polishing off the remainder for lunch today.

