This recipe is a good starting point. Storebought polenta would be very fast and is not that expensive, but I made my own (6 cups water, 3 cups polenta - makes a lot, but the extra is good for so many things). As other reviewers suggested, I whisked sour cream with milk as a substitute for the cream. (Not sure what part that really plays in the dish, but hey...can't hurt.) I can't imagine making this recipe exactly as is with no onions. I sauteed one onion, 1/2 a red bell pepper (just because I had it in the fridge), some minced hot pepper, and lots of mushrooms then added the salsa verde, garlic, and spices to that mix. I layered polenta, beans, veggie mix, cheese (x2). Next time, I'll mix the beans with the veggies and do that as one layer and add a thick layer of salsa or tomatoes - we agreed that it needs the extra flavor and juice. Cooking times were about right - I only did 10 minutes without the foil instead of 15. I have a feeling the people who thought the dish looked messy didn't give it time to cool and set. Our first servings (five minutes out of the oven) were very messy, yes. Once the dish had rested 30, though, and I was putting it into tupperware for lunch, it sliced and 'served' beautifully.

